The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, August 23, 2004 				 Rail officer sacked for fake jobs 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Malda, Aug. 22: The senior welfare inspector of Eastern Railways Malda division has been dismissed from service for trying to provide jobs to three youths on compassionate grounds.																								The railway said V.P. Singh had tried to secure jobs for the youths from Bihar as group-D employees claiming that their fathers had died in service.																								The youths were handed forged appointment letters and asked to report to the rail hospital here for medical tests. Hospital superintendent Sanjib Ghosal, who felt something was amiss, informed officers about the appointments. 																								It has been established that the inspector tried to give jobs illegally, the railway said.
